http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/Visakhapatnam/Bharat-Forge-to-invest-Rs.-1200-cr.-in-Nellore/article13993869.ece

Leading forging major Bharat Forge on Sunday announced plans to set up an integrated auto components hub in Nellore at an investment of around Rs. 1,200 crore.The firm signed an Memorandum of Understanding (MoU) with the Government of Andhra Pradesh at the inaugural of thee three-day CII Partnership Summit and Sunrise AP Investment Meet.“We plan to set up a fairly large integrated automotive component manufacturing hub in Nellore district with an investment of about Rs. 1,200 crore and will employ 3,000 and odd people directly and almost similar number of people indirectly. Hopefully, we will create a substantial ancillary economic structure,” Bharat Forge Chairman Baba Kalyani said. Announcing to the plans, Mr. Kalyani, who is also the chairman of CII National Committee on Defence, said another MoU had also been signed with the State to set up a multi-modal facility.“Second, we propose to make a multi-modal manufacturing facility for industrial components, defence and aerospace components including a supply chain and this will be located in Anantapur district,” he said.He said that for both these locations, the company has already finalised the land. “I think in the next few weeks, we will actually get physical possession of the land and start our work,” he said.Pune-based Bharat Forge is the world’s largest forging company with manufacturing facilities spread across India, Germany, Sweden and France. It manufactures a wide range of components for the automotive and non-automotive sectors.(With inputs from PTI)We propose a multi-modal manufacturing facility for industrial components, defence and aerospace components in Anantapur.- Baba Kalyani,Bharat Forge Chairman